    {
      "id": "7dd6e4f2ce11374c4338810857600d3da490d027",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-08-06 20:03:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI don't think it is safe to simply send all of the requests in a single set, unless ptlrpcd is modified to limit the number of RPCs in flight. Otherwise I recall it could block all of the service threads on the target.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "d7e16cb866b81f10dd3fb15cfeca288575c15440",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2011-08-07 00:03:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nActually I am not sure how the target's threads would be blocked in this scenario.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "873253b2bbfad7e904e61e281942ea60b1480e62",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-08-07 00:40:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI don't recall the exact details, but I think Johann might. Something like:\n\n- target sends num_callbacks > num_threads\n- all threads are blocked waiting for the same lock\n- callbacks are not processed because all threads are block\n\nI'm not sure this is correct, but I recall something like this.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "caddcfd4d884e1a22bd5cb9a551313aa598df3d8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-08-08 18:58:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nBut I really need this feature for IR. Is it okay to apply an unlimited RPC parallel limit for MGS case, and keep 200 for others?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
